# Architecture and patterns

## Host app wiring (sample is reference)
- `sample/*` is the reference host application and is allowed to do runtime wiring:
  - instantiate `CommonComponent` / feature components
  - pass runtime config like `baseUrl`
  - register `AppErrorParser` feature parsers in `CommonComponent.init(...)`
  - register WebSocket message handlers
- SDK modules (`core/*`, `feature/*`) must not assume the host entry point; they should be usable by any app that provides the required constructor parameters.

## Networking (Ktor client + WebSockets)
- HTTP client bootstrap:
  - Common default configuration is applied in `core/common` via `HttpClientCommonConfig.setupCommonConfig(...)`.
  - Additional client behavior must be expressed as `HttpClientConfigPlugin` implementations (in the owning module).
- WebSockets:
  - SDK provides WebSocket plumbing in `core/common` (`KtorWebSocketService` + base message handler wiring).
  - Feature-specific message interpretation belongs in `WebSocketMessageHandler` implementations in the corresponding module.

## Error modeling and parsing
- Errors are modeled as `AppError` implementations with:
  - a stable machine-readable `code`
  - optional `args` map with additional metadata
  - an `isRetryable` flag
- Parsing to user-facing strings is done via `AppErrorParser`:
  - `CommonErrorParser` is the fallback authority for common codes.
  - Feature parsers (e.g. user/security) map their codes to localized `composeResources` strings.

## Layering (keep responsibilities separated)
- Prefer this general flow:
  - Compose UI / Decompose components
  - use cases (or use-case modules)
  - repositories (network/storage orchestration)
  - storage abstractions + network clients
- Repositories should be responsible for:
  - calling network endpoints / parsing responses
  - mapping failures into `AppError` / `AppResult.Error`
- Decompose components (presentation layer) own screen state and trigger actions:
  - they call use cases/repositories via injected collaborators
  - they translate `AppResult`/errors into `*ScreenState` (or an equivalent state model)
- UI composables (render layer) should only:
  - render the current screen state
  - call user-intent handlers exposed by the Decompose component
  - display localized strings via `AppErrorParser` (e.g. via `CompositionLocal` helpers)

## Configuration & runtime parameters
- Runtime config values (e.g. `baseUrl`) must be passed via constructor parameters into components/modules.
- Avoid hardcoding environment values inside `core/*` or `feature/*` modules.

## Naming / packaging
- Package by layer/feature, using existing conventions from this repo:
  - `ui/`, `model/`, `usecase/`, `repository/`, `storage/`, `network/`, `error/`, `di/`
  - if a dedicated `config` package exists in some module, follow that module’s local convention
- Use module prefixes in resource string ids:
  - `error_common_*`, `error_user_*`, `error_security_*`.
